doc.previous: Commuter rail type service directly from a city centre to the airport without needing to change trains and sometimes without intermediate stops  In some airports such as San Francisco International Airport the rail link only serves one terminal or concourse directly passengers using other terminals must use an people mover airport circulator Circulators typically also serve parking lots and sometimes airport hotels and off site car rental locations
